@vars = ('P','P','L','L','S','S');
Context()->variables->are(P => 'Real', L => 'Real', S => 'Real');

@coefs = num_sort((2..50)[NchooseK(49,6)]);
@terms = ();
for my $i (1..6) {
  push(@terms, Formula("$coefs[$i-1]*$vars[$i-1]")->reduce);
}
$one = Formula("$coefs[0] P + $coefs[2] L + $coefs[4] S");
$two = Formula("$coefs[1] P + $coefs[3] L + $coefs[5] S");
$ans = Formula("($coefs[0] + $coefs[1]) P + ($coefs[2] + $coefs[3]) L +  ($coefs[4] + $coefs[5]) S");

Context("Form");
Context()->variables->are(P => 'Real', L => 'Real', S => 'Real');

$ans = Formula("$ans");

############################################################
# Body
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML
Sportsball is a game similar to basketball. There are three ways for a team to score points: a "long field goal" earns [`L`] points; a "short field goal" earns [`S`] points; and a "penalty shot" earns [`P`] points.

In the first half of one game, a team scored [`[$coefs[0]]`] penalty shots, [`[$coefs[2]]`] long field goals, and [`[$coefs[4]]`] short field goals. So they earned [`[$one]`] points.

END_PGML

